abstract: Turkish military says more than 49 Kurdish insurgents were killed in first two days of offensive against Kurdish Worker's Party rebels in southeastern Turkey and northern Iraq; campaign has strained relations between neighboring countries.
snippet: A military campaign in southeastern Turkey and northern Iraq has strained relations between the neighbors.
lead_paragraph: A military campaign in southeastern Turkey and northern Iraq has strained relations between the neighbors.

headline.main: Turkey Says It Killed 49 in Battling Kurd Rebels

headline.seo: Turkey Says It Killed 49 in Offensive Against Kurdish Rebels
